      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IOWNA BENZ (6) led and went on to score by 1.3 lengths last time out over 1000m in a 66 at Wagga. Was heavily bet and had been busting to win. Tumbles in weight at this level, and that brings her right into it. Maps well and can go on with it. TEYLU (1) resumes for the local Vella yard and delivered a hat-trick at Wagga when last seen. He can use the rail and has a sharp record at this course and distance. A bold return is on the cards. PANIC (4) found the line nicely to get up for second over 1000m this grade at the track/trip. Will drift back but wind up late, and Collett sticking aboard is a positive. It's been 410 days without success for KEIKOKU (2), but he's been busting to win here at this level and dropping back 200m has to be considered again. PARTY DOLL (7) placed in the same contest and has the blinkers on again. She's also hard to catch but can't be ruled out.",
